msgid "Translation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../translation.rst:4
msgid ""
"The PyCon site is set up for use in English and French, for the most part."
msgstr ""

#: ../../translation.rst:7
msgid "Which language is displayed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../translation.rst:9
msgid ""
"By default, the request headers control which language is displayed. A user "
"can change their brower's settings to say what their preferred languages "
"are, and if French comes before English, the site will use French when "
"available. It'll fall back to English for text that isn't translated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../translation.rst:14
msgid ""
"A language selector can optionally be displayed on the Dashboard page. This "
"allows a user to temporarily override the displayed language for the current"
" session. Whether the language selector is displayed is controlled by the "
"django-constance setting SHOW_LANGUAGE_SELECTOR, which can be changed in the"
" admin at /YEAR/admin/constance/config/."
msgstr ""

#: ../../translation.rst:21
msgid "Translating"
msgstr ""

#: ../../translation.rst:23
msgid ""
"For CMS pages, there are two body fields. The first is for English. The "
"second is for French. You'll have to scroll down a ways to see it when "
"editing a CMS page."
msgstr ""

#: ../../translation.rst:27
msgid ""
"Text on most other pages, forms, etc is translatable using Django's "
"internationalization support. To add or update translations, a developer "
"would:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../translation.rst:31
msgid ""
"set up a local development environment for PyCon according to the README"
msgstr ""

#: ../../translation.rst:32
msgid "make a new branch off the `develop` branch"
msgstr ""

#: ../../translation.rst:33
msgid "make sure you have Gnu gettext installed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../translation.rst:34
msgid "install fabric: ``pip install fabric``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../translation.rst:35
msgid ""
"run ``fab make_messages`` to update the .po files, in case any translatable "
"text has changed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../translation.rst:37
msgid ""
"edit ``locale/fr/LC_MESSAGES/django.po``, filling in ``msgstr`` with the "
"translated version of whatever text is in the ``msgid`` just above it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../translation.rst:39
msgid ""
"run ``fab compile_messages`` to update the .mo file with the new "
"translations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../translation.rst:41
msgid "commit the updated .po and .mo files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../translation.rst:42
msgid "open a pull request against the main repo to get your updates included"
msgstr ""

#: ../../translation.rst:44
msgid ""
"If a non-developer is going to help with translation, a developer could do "
"all the steps except editing the .po file, just sending the .po file to the "
"translator for them to edit and send back."
msgstr ""

#: ../../translation.rst:48
msgid ""
"Any text not translated in the translation files will be displayed as "
"English."
msgstr ""
